The reelection bid of President Muhammadu Buhari and the chances of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) to retain power in the 2019 general elections today become slimmer. This is as the break away faction of APC code named the ” reformed All Progressives Congress, reAPC is currently meeting  in Abuja with the main opposition, Peoples Democratic, Party, PDP and other political parties under the auspices of Coalition of United Political Parties, CUPP to sign a Memorandum of Understanding, MOU. Business Day gathered that the MOU titled, ” Rescue Nigeria Grand Alliance ” among others seeks to present a consensus President Candidate to wrestle power from Buhari/ APC. Details later…